          "event": "chat_node_completed",
          "userId": "f43ac274-e715-457a-93ff-f92bb660c754",
          "content": "{\n  \"type\": \"final\",\n  \"message\": \"Whisky from Scotland is known as Scotch whisky. It is a type of whisky that is distilled and aged in Scotland. There are several types of Scotch whisky, including single malt, single grain, blended malt, blended grain, and blended Scotch whisky. The most well-known types are single malt and blended Scotch. Scotch whisky must be aged in oak barrels for at least three years and must have an alcohol content of at least 40% ABV (alcohol by volume). The Scotch Whisky Regulations 2009 define the requirements for a whisky to be labeled as Scotch.\"\n}",
